---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Founder-Built Web Systems for Operational Clarity"
  description="DRN.today builds internal web systems that replace spreadsheets, reduce operational friction, and bring clarity â€” designed and executed by a single accountable founder."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0a0a0f 0%, #111118 100%); padding: 120px 24px; text-align: center;">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h1 style="font-size: 3.5rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 24px; background: linear-gradient(90deg, #f0f0f5 0%, #b0b0c0 100%); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;">From Operational Chaos to Clarity</h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: #b0b0c0; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 48px; max-width: 600px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
        Founder-built internal systems that replace spreadsheets, reduce friction, and bring control to your business operations.
      </p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/contact" style="background: #3a8bba; color: white; padding: 16px 32px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1rem; display: inline-block;">Describe Your System Challenge</a>
        <a href="#how-i-work" style="background: transparent; color: #3a8bba; padding: 15px 31px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1rem; display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #3a8bba;">Schedule a Clarity Call</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem Recognition Section -->
  <section style="padding: 80px 24px; max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 48px; text-align: center;">When Spreadsheets Stop Working</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 32px;">
      <div style="background: #1a1a23; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 6px; padding: 32px;">
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #f0f0f5;">Manual Data Reconciliation</h3>
        <p style="color: #b0b0c0; line-height: 1.6;">Hours spent daily merging data from multiple spreadsheets and tools that don't communicate.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background: #1a1a23; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 6px; padding: 32px;">
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #f0f0f5;">Lack of Real-time Visibility</h3>
        <p style="color: #b0b0c0; line-height: 1.6;">Decisions made with outdated information because there's no single source of truth.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background: #1a1a23; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 6px; padding: 32px;">
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #f0f0f5;">Founder Dependency</h3>
        <p style="color: #b0b0c0; line-height: 1.6;">You're the bottleneck because only you know how all the pieces fit together.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How I Work Section -->
  <section id="how-i-work" style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, #111118 0%, #0a0a0f 100%); padding: 80px 24px;">
    <div style="max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 48px; text-align: center;">How I Work: Execution Without Hand-Offs</h2>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 32px;">
        <div style="background: #1a1a23; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 6px; padding: 32px;">
          <div style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: #3a8bba; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 16px;">01</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #f0f0f5;">Single-Point Ownership</h3>
          <p style="color: #b0b0c0; line-height: 1.6;">From first line of code to deployment and long-term maintenance. No hand-offs, no excuses.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background: #1a1a23; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 6px; padding: 32px;">
          <div style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: #3a8bba; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 16px;">02</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #f0f0f5;">Systems for Daily Use</h3>
          <p style="color: #b0b0c0; line-height: 1.6;">Built for reliability in daily operations, not as demos or prototypes that fail under real load.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background: #1a1a23; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 6px; padding: 32px;">
          <div style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: #3a8bba; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 16px;">03</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #f0f0f5;">Stability Before Scale</h3>
          <p style="color: #b0b0c0; line-height: 1.6;">A working system for 100 users is better than a broken one for 1000. Reliability first.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background: #1a1a23; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 6px; padding: 32px;">
          <div style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: #3a8bba; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 16px;">04</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #f0f0f5;">No Scope Creep</h3>
          <p style="color: #b0b0c0; line-height: 1.6;">Controlled, intentional evolution. We build what's needed, not everything that's possible.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background: #1a1a23; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 6px; padding: 32px;">
          <div style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: #3a8bba; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 16px;">05</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #f0f0f5;">Decisions Documented</h3>
          <p style="color: #b0b0c0; line-height: 1.6;">Trade-offs explained, architecture reasoned. You understand why we built it this way.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background: #1a1a23; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 6px; padding: 32px;">
          <div style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: #3a8bba; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 16px;">06</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #f0f0f5;">Long-Term Responsibility</h3>
          <p style="color: #b0b0c0; line-height: 1.6;">What I build, I maintain. Your system evolves with your business, doesn't get abandoned.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA Section -->
  <section style="padding: 80px 24px; text-align: center;">
    <div style="max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px;">Ready to Systematize Your Operations?</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; color: #b0b0c0; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 48px;">
        Stop patching broken processes. Start building systems that work.
      </p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/contact" style="background: #3a8bba; color: white; padding: 16px 32px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1rem; display: inline-block;">Describe Your System Challenge</a>
        <a href="#how-i-work" style="background: transparent; color: #3a8bba; padding: 15px 31px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1rem; display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #3a8bba;">Schedule a 20-Minute Call</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
